## Checklist

Before declaring a pip package complete:

- [ ] `__init__.py` gates `extension.py` import behind `try/except ImportError`
- [ ] No module-level `omni.*` or Kit-only schema imports in non-extension files
- [ ] `pxr` submodules explicitly imported (not relying on Kit's transitive imports)
- [ ] `[tool.standalone-wheel] symlinks` declared for Pattern B/C layouts
- [ ] `pyproject.toml` uses `packages.find` with explicit `include`/`exclude`
- [ ] Non-Python data files declared in `[tool.setuptools.package-data]`
- [ ] Version matches `extension.toml`
- [ ] `./repo.sh build_standalone_wheels --ext <name>` succeeds
- [ ] Wheel contains files under correct namespace with NO `__init__.py` at intermediate levels
- [ ] Data files present in wheel (verify with `unzip -l`)
- [ ] Tests excluded from wheel
- [ ] `standalone_tests/test_smoke.py` exists and passes
- [ ] Clean venv install + import works with only `usd-core`
- [ ] Import path is identical to Kit
- [ ] No `omni.*` modules loaded after import
- [ ] `./repo.sh build_standalone_wheels --clean --test` passes

